<div id="right">
    <div class="padding">
      <h1>About CERIT-SC</h1>
      <p class="path"> <a href="/en/about/">About CERIT-SC</a>
</p>
 <!-- Content -->
<p>Center CERIT-SC was created through a transformation of the <a target="_self" href="/en/about/History/index.html">Supercomputing Center Brno (SCB)</a>, part of the <a target="_blank" href="http://ics.muni.cz/">Institute of Computer Science (ICS, ÃšVT in Czech</a>) at <a href="http://www.muni.cz">Masaryk University</a>. Center CERIT-SC still stays a part of ICS, with a degree of independence corresponding to the needs and requirements of implementing <a href="/en/about/VaVpI/">an OP VaVpI project</a> that is funding the first phase of the transformation.</p>
<p>Center CERIT-SC is an importnat part of the national e-Infrastructure, a  complex system of mutually interconnected network, computing, and  storage resources and corresponding services for the zech research  community. This role of the Centrum CERIT-SC is explicitly mentioned in  the <a href="http://www.msmt.cz/vyzkum/schvaleny-text-cestovni-mapy">Roadmap of large infrastructures for research, development, and  innovations in the Czech Republic</a>. CERIT-SC resources and services  offered and its research targets complement two other parts of the  approved national e-Infrastructure &ndash; <a href="http://www.cesnet.cz">CESNET</a> and the <a href="http://www.it4i.eu">supercomputing center IT4Innovations</a>. Center will become the largest node of the <a href="http://metacentrum.cz">National Grid infrastructure</a>, with emphasis on advanced services and cooperation between grid and cloud services.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p><!-- Footer -->
